<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aalarie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hi everyone!<P>I think there is a problem with this spell. When I got this spell and cast it I did not recieve a icon. So I thought the spell was broken. Then I started recieveing text that said soAndso was near me. Still had no icon. So i thought that it must be a fixed duration spell. That would not have been a problem. <P>The problem is when ever you get near someone it auto targets them! It is a pain in the rear. I have my tank targeted about to cast Gheal then someone runs bye me and they are tageted not my tank. See where this can become a problem. Also I no longer recieve any text messages saying soAndso is near me. So I looked up the spell and it has a 10 hour duration!!! That is 10 hours with no way to turn it off!<P>Is this a bug or is the spell broken?? Here is the spell information for Casters Realm:<P>Name:  Sanctuary <BR>Level:  9 <BR>Mana:  25 <BR>Class:  Divination <BR>Era:  Shadows Of Luclin <BR>Vendor(s):  Unknown <BR>Approx Spell Cost:  Unknown <BR>Researchable:  No <BR>Type:  General Purpose <BR>Max Duration:  10 hours <BR>Casting Time:  2.5 seconds <BR>Recast Time:  5 seconds <BR>Actual Effects: Area: Undead Alert <BR>Description: A modified sentinal spell, this will alert you whenever a creature or player approaches you. Good to use while meditating for safety, although the spell has been known to be a bit heavy on text messages. <P>Is anyone else having this problem?<P>Thank you in advance.<P>Aalarie<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's basically an annoying spell with little use ;p  I didn't notice the autotarget, but then I tried it out while sitting at the wizzy spires waiting for one of my groupmates.  The 10 hours is game time, not real life, so less then 15 minutes real time.  Which is still a bit long for something you are only likely to use while medding and solo (rather rare for a cleric).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">That is exactly the way it is supposted to work Aalarie.  Why they gave this to clerics I will never know.<P>Aladain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Even with Paritical effects on full I don't see a thing when this spell is cast.  That's what really pisses me off about it... yeah it's annoying, and trust me... your group will hate you for casting it... but atleast when enchanter's get sentinel they can put on a pretty light show.  WTF!  I've played my brother's enchanter and just had fun casting 4 sentinel's and running amok in the color's... but this sanctuary is a complete waste of 3pp.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sollwin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">VI still does not get the "we would rather not have a spell than some useless peice of CRAP"<P>I mean, look at the pet spell, USELESS, except to get a laugh out of folks.  Then we get this steaming pile.  Might was well have not even given us a spell at that level, all they did was manage to insult us.<P>THIS is their idea of a NEW SoL spell? Regurgitated CRAP from a spell that was rarely if ever used by the class they gave it to in the first place.<P>------------------<BR>Sollwin Lifestar<BR>58th Halfling Templar of Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41743" TARGET=_blank>Inspect Me!</A></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
